Iavan Pijoos, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; Two sisters were stabbed to death and three others sustained multiple stab wounds during a house robbery in the early hours of Wednesday morning, police said.&nbsp;Captain Ilze Jones said one of the women arrived at the house on Main Street in Garsfontein in Pretoria, where she was confronted by a knife-wielding man outside who forced her into the house.&nbsp;"She arrived at around 20:00 on Tuesday evening, but the rest of the people were already held up by three men," Jones said.Police were only called to the scene at midnight on Wednesday evening.&nbsp;Jones said the three men had stabbed the two sisters to death and left a 59-year-old man, who is believed to be the owner of the house, in a critical condition. &nbsp;Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said, when paramedics arrived at the scene around 00:46 on Wednesday morning, they found that the people had been tied up, assaulted and stabbed.&nbsp;Botha said one other woman had been seriously injured, while a fourth woman had sustained moderate injuries.&nbsp;They were taken to hospital.The robbers fled the scene with two televisions and one vehicle that was later recovered in Yeoville, Johannesburg.No arrests had been made. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.